headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet set a franchise record with 54 points and hit a career-best 11 3-pointers as the Toronto Raptors beat the short-handed Orlando Magic 123-108 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: VanVleet sets Raptors mark with 54 in 123-108 win at Orlando

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving scored a season-high 39 points, including eight straight in the fourth-quarter run that sent Brooklyn into the lead for good, and the Nets beat the Los Angeles Clippers 124-120 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Irving scores 39, Nets cool off Clippers with 124-120 win

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had a season-high 32 points and 13 rebounds Tuesday night as the Indiana Pacers beat Memphis 134-116, snapping the Grizzlies' seven-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers top Memphis 134-116, snap Grizzlies' 7-game streak

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard scored 32 points, Gary Trent Jr. added 26 while hitting seven 3-pointers and the short-handed Portland Trail Blazers held on for a 132-121 victory over the Washington Wizards on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard leads short-handed Blazers past Wizards, 132-121

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 32 points to lead the Utah Jazz to a 117-105 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz survive late rally, edge Pistons 117-105

events.name: Boston Celtics at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum had 27 points in picking up the offensive slack for Boston without injured Marcus Smart, and the Celtics withstood another scoring outburst by Stephen Curry to beat the Golden State Warriors 111-107 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum, Celtics hold off Curry and Warriors for 111-107 win
